  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-gray-900 mb-6">Resources for Attendees</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-10">
      Welcome to the 2025 DLF Forum! This guide includes essential resources and expectations to help you prepare for a safe, inclusive, and engaging experience.
    </p>

    <!-- Shared Notes -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Shared Notes</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Collaborate and share your session notes with other attendees using our shared Google Drive folder:
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1aNG1Y5knDys7QTNL0qEdpMqWYSXb1TK6" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Access the Shared Notes Folder</a>
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Zenodo Community</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Explore and share research outputs, presentations, and materials from the DLF Forum community through our Zenodo hub:
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <a href="https://zenodo.org/communities/dlf-forum" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Visit the DLF Forum Zenodo Community</a>
    </p>

    <!-- Code of Conduct -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Code of Conduct</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      All attendees are expected to adhere to the <a href="https://www.diglib.org/about/code-of-conduct/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">DLF Code of Conduct</a>, which outlines our commitment to providing a welcoming and harassment-free environment for everyone.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      DLF staff will be identifiable by their name badges and <strong>white lanyards</strong>. Please do not hesitate to reach out if you need support or witness behavior that violates the Code.
    </p>

    <!-- Active Bystander Training -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Active Bystander Training</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      We encourage all participants to watch our Active Bystander Training session. It provides tools for safely intervening in situations of harassment or bias, aligning with our values of community care and mutual respect.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oHUfMpqxK8Y" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Watch the training video</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/11TzOpJE0_p5e47dGXLK1gpHbrLQqdME7eHPCjZZt69I/export/pdf" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Download the slides (PDF)</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      The training was created by DLF’s Committee for Equity and Inclusion. All attendees are strongly encouraged to review it before the event.
    </p>

    <!-- Health Protocols -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Health Protocols</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      We are committed to providing a safe environment for all participants. Our health practices include:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li>Masks are welcome and encouraged based on personal comfort.</li>
      <li>Masks and hand sanitizer will be available at the registration desk.</li>
      <li>A designated quiet space will be available for rest and breaks.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      If you have any health-related concerns or accessibility needs, please contact us at <a href="mailto:forum@diglib.org" class="underline text-blue-700">forum@diglib.org</a>.
    </p>

    <!-- Photography Guidelines -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Photography Guidelines</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      We respect attendees’ preferences when it comes to being photographed or recorded. When registering, attendees can indicate their preferences, which are visible via lanyard color:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li>
        <strong>Black lanyards:</strong> Okay to photograph</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Yellow lanyards:</strong> Do not photograph</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Please always ask for consent before taking photos, videos, or recordings of others. Respect and care are foundational to our community.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-gray-900 mt-16 mb-6">Resources for Families</h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mb-4">Nursing Room</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      We will provide a nursing room onsite for those who prefer a quiet, private place to breastfeed their baby or pump. However, please feed your baby whenever and wherever you like. We strive to be a friendly environment for families.  
      Please ask for the key to the nursing room at the conference registration desk. This room is accessible to one family at a time and is located in a private room away from the conference spaces.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Childcare and Family Activities</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      While we are not able to provide onsite childcare at the DLF Forum this year, the planning team has compiled a list of resources that may help.
    </p>

    <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Local babysitter agencies & referral services</h4>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 italic">
      * Please Note: Many of these agencies will require registration in advance. We would encourage you to ask about background checks, references, and liability insurance.
    </p>

    <h5 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mb-2">
      <a href="https://babysittersofboulder.com/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Babysitters of Boulder</a>
    </h5>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Visitor pricing is <a href="https://babysittersofboulder.com/visitor-pricing/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">here</a>. To register for care:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li>Complete registration form <a href="https://babysittersofboulder.com/signup-for-service/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">here</a> and select "vacation/visitor" as type in question 1</li>
      <li>Submit registration form, $75 registration fee applied</li>
      <li>Parent will be able to log into their new account and place booking requests for Nov 16–19</li>
      <li>Care includes a $35 per day booking fee, and $35 per hour to sitter.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      All of our sitters are CPR Certified, have 5+ years of experience, complete a background and DMV record check every 3 years. Our service includes a substitute as well, in the rare event a sitter must cancel, so parents can have confidence that childcare is arranged while they attend the conference.
    </p>

    <h5 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mb-2">
      <a href="https://www.jovie.com/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Jovie: nannies + sitters</a>
    </h5>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Starts at $42.95/hour (plus parking fees for your caregiver).<br>
      Be sure to book by Nov 1st.<br>
      Flyer: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cjCKnEYjgqmcaSPyVwETsRJIfZ1FZNM1/view?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Resources for Families_Jovie.pdf</a>
    </p>

    <h5 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mb-2">
      <a href="https://www.care.com/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Care.com</a>
    </h5>
    <h5 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mb-4">
      <a href="https://www.goinstacare.com/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">GoInstaCare</a>
    </h5>

    <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">Family-Friendly Activities</h4>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      If your kids are lucky enough to join you in Denver, make sure to block out some time to explore some of these great family-friendly spots:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <a href="https://denverzoo.org/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Denver Zoo</a><br>
        If you are in Denver on Nov 15th, be sure to take advantage of Denver Zoo’s Free Community Days. <a href="https://denverzoo.org/free-days/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Visit this page</a> to register for your free day tickets – tickets will be released on November 4th.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.aquariumrestaurants.com/downtownaquariumdenver/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Downtown Aquarium</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://moidenver.com/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Museum of Illusions – Denver</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.mychildsmuseum.org/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Children’s Museum of Denver at Marsico Campus</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.dmns.org/" target="_blank" class="underline text-blue-700">Denver Museum of Nature and Science</a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Other Resources -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Support Line</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      If you need immediate help or want to report an issue during the event, please use our dedicated support line:
    </p>
    <p class="font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mb-2">
      (732) 737-7328 — That’s (732) RESPECT
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      This line is monitored daily between 7:00 AM and 9:00 PM in the event’s local time zone by CLIR/DLF staff.
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-700">
      For general questions, you can always email us at <a href="mailto:forum@diglib.org" class="underline text-blue-700">forum@diglib.org</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

